## üéì Educational Value

### OOP Principles Demonstrated

‚úÖ **Encapsulation** - Data hiding with properties  
‚úÖ **Abstraction** - Abstract base classes (Monitor, Observer, Repository)  
‚úÖ **Inheritance** - Monitor hierarchy, Observer hierarchy  
‚úÖ **Polymorphism** - Platform-specific implementations  

### SOLID Principles

‚úÖ **Single Responsibility** - Each class has one job  
‚úÖ **Open/Closed** - Easy to extend without modification  
‚úÖ **Liskov Substitution** - Subclasses can replace parents  
‚úÖ **Interface Segregation** - Focused interfaces  
‚úÖ **Dependency Inversion** - Depend on abstractions  

### Statistics

- **42+ classes** - Comprehensive OOP structure
- **10+ design patterns** - Real-world pattern usage
- **~2,800 lines of code** - Production-quality implementation
- **5 anomaly types** - All testable with provided scripts
- **Cross-platform** - Works on Windows and Linux
- **Zero database knowledge required** - Uses simple CSV files

